## first release
this first release includes working version of the chess console game. This version includes the following features:
- [x] Chess pieces can be moved on the board, captured, promoted, castled, en passant captured, checkmated, and stalemated.
- [x] The game can be played against the computer.
- [x] The game can be played against another player.
- [x] The game can be played in a console window.
- [x] The game has a set of illegal moves that the player cannot make.

User Stories completed:
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to play a game of chess against the computer.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to move the chess pieces on the board.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to see the chess pieces of the board in the console.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to win by checkmate, and lose by checkmate.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to win by stalemate, and lose by stalemate.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to win by castling,  and lose by castling.

## Second release
This second release includes a working version of the chess console game. This version has a lot of changes from the first release. This version includes changes to all pieces, the board, and the game. The strategy pattern has been included.

User stories completed:
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to choose the color of the pieces.
- [x] As a user, I want to be able to play against another player on the same PC.